				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Maximum DPS possible?<a name="26827"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 8:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well first of all, as far as I know, a warrior is not a massive DPS class itself.  They hold aggro with a decent DPS and taunting.
<br />

<br />
I think a bard could surpass a warrior of the same lvl fairly easily.  I am thinking of dual wielding, one weapon being a percussion instrument, and twisting chant of flame &amp; fufil's curtaling chant with a haste song while wearing FBSS (or someother haste item).
<br />

<br />
I could be wrong, but I think we could out DPS a warrior pretty easily.  It is the other dps classes that would be a challenge.  Rogues as a secondary fighter is very dangerous.  I hear beastlords are high in dps... i guess with the pet, melee, and spells they must put up so good numbers.  Rangers i think too, cause they can melee and cast.
<br />

<br />
I am interested to see what the rest of you thing on this too.</span></td>
